{
  "info": {
    "name": "Apigee — OAuth2 Authorization Code + PKCE",
    "description": "Emula el flujo OAuth2 + PKCE que implementa el portal (ver docs/apigee-auth-flow.md).\n\nNo necesita navegador: el /authorize de Apigee devuelve el code sin login ni consentimiento, así que todo se resuelve con peticiones HTTP puras. El iframe y el componente de callback que usa la app existen para capturar el redirect en el navegador; aquí el redirect ni siquiera se sigue.\n\nUSO: ejecutar la colección con el Collection Runner, o los dos requests EN ORDEN. El code es de un solo uso y caduca rápido: no sirve reejecutar el /token sin volver a pasar por el /authorize.\n\nIMPORTANTE: `1. authorize` tiene los redirects DESACTIVADOS a propósito (protocolProfileBehavior.followRedirects=false). El code viaja en la cabecera Location del 302; si Postman siguiera el redirect, se perdería.\n\nVerificada con: newman run docs/postman/apigee-pkce.postman_collection.json",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "authUrl",
      "value": "https://api.latam.cloud.cardifnet.com/oauth2/v1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "clientId",
      "value": "XjuYyYC1jSNuZMP0zEjveBpNGldiO1fAl42MxKaYdY4zCABm",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "redirectUri",
      "value": "https://oi-auto-cla.latam.cloud.cardifnet.com/callback",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Debe estar registrado como callback en la app de Apigee. Aquí el navegador nunca lo visita: solo tiene que coincidir entre el authorize y el token."
    },
    {
      "key": "scope",
      "value": "foo",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "idp",
      "value": "noidp",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "codeVerifier",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "codeChallenge",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "state",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "code",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "accessToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. authorize (genera PKCE y obtiene el code)",
      "protocolProfileBehavior": {
        "followRedirects": false
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// Genera las credenciales PKCE (RFC 7636), igual que src/app/features/auth/services/pkce.ts",
              "// CryptoJS ya es global en el sandbox de Postman: redeclararlo con",
              "// `const CryptoJS = require(...)` lanza 'already been declared'.",
              "const CJS = require('crypto-js');",
              "",
              "const toB64Url = (wa) => CJS.enc.Base64.stringify(wa)",
              "  .replace(/\\+/g, '-').replace(/\\//g, '_').replace(/=/g, '');",
              "",
              "// verifier: 32 bytes aleatorios -> 43 chars (el RFC exige 43-128)",
              "const verifier = toB64Url(CJS.lib.WordArray.random(32));",
              "// challenge: base64url(SHA-256(verifier)) = método S256",
              "const challenge = toB64Url(CJS.SHA256(verifier));",
              "// state: nonce anti-CSRF, debe volver idéntico",
              "const state = toB64Url(CJS.lib.WordArray.random(12));",
              "",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('codeVerifier', verifier);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('codeChallenge', challenge);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('state', state);",
              "",
              "console.log('verifier :', verifier);",
              "console.log('challenge:', challenge);"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// El code viaja en la cabecera Location del 302, no en el body.",
              "pm.test('302 (si da 400, revisa redirect_uri/client_id)', function () {",
              "  if (pm.response.code === 400) {",
              "    console.log('Respuesta:', pm.response.text());",
              "  }",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(302);",
              "});",
              "",
              "const location = pm.response.headers.get('Location');",
              "pm.test('trae cabecera Location', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(location).to.be.a('string');",
              "});",
              "",
              "if (location) {",
              "  // El sandbox de Postman no tiene URLSearchParams: se parsea a mano.",
              "  const pick = (name) => {",
              "    const m = location.match(new RegExp('[?&]' + name + '=([^&]*)'));",
              "    return m ? decodeURIComponent(m[1]) : null;",
              "  };",
              "  const code = pick('code');",
              "  const returnedState = pick('state');",
              "",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('code', code);",
              "",
              "  pm.test('el state vuelve idéntico (anti-CSRF)', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(returnedState).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('state'));",
              "  });",
              "  pm.test('devuelve un code', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(code).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "  });",
              "",
              "  console.log('code:', code);",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Accept",
            "value": "*/*"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{authUrl}}/authorize?response_type=code&client_id={{clientId}}&code_challenge_method=S256&code_challenge={{codeChallenge}}&redirect_uri={{redirectUri}}&scope={{scope}}&idp={{idp}}&state={{state}}",
          "host": [
            "{{authUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "authorize"
          ],
          "query": [
            {
              "key": "response_type",
              "value": "code"
            },
            {
              "key": "client_id",
              "value": "{{clientId}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "code_challenge_method",
              "value": "S256"
            },
            {
              "key": "code_challenge",
              "value": "{{codeChallenge}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "redirect_uri",
              "value": "{{redirectUri}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "scope",
              "value": "{{scope}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "idp",
              "value": "{{idp}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "state",
              "value": "{{state}}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "description": "Paso 1. Redirects desactivados: el code está en la cabecera Location del 302."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. token (canjea el code por el access_token)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () {",
              "  if (pm.response.code !== 200) console.log('Respuesta:', pm.response.text());",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('devuelve access_token', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "pm.test('token_type Bearer', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(json.token_type).to.eql('Bearer');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.access_token);",
              "console.log('access_token:', json.access_token, '| expira en', json.expires_in, 's');"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "urlencoded",
          "urlencoded": [
            {
              "key": "grant_type",
              "value": "authorization_code"
            },
            {
              "key": "code",
              "value": "{{code}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "redirect_uri",
              "value": "{{redirectUri}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "client_id",
              "value": "{{clientId}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "code_verifier",
              "value": "{{codeVerifier}}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{authUrl}}/token",
          "host": [
            "{{authUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "token"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Paso 3. El redirect_uri debe ser idéntico al del authorize (no se visita, solo se compara). El code_verifier es lo que prueba que somos quienes iniciamos el flujo."
      }
    }
  ]
}
